olive oil
½ carrot
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 leek
1 cucumber
1 bag mint
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet beef strips
1 packet mango chutney
¾ cup water
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Mumbai Spice Blend

• Grate carrot (see ingredients). Thinly slice leek.
• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat.
Cook carrot and leek, stirring, until softened, 2 minutes.
• Add the water and chicken-style stock powder and bring to the boil.
• Add couscous, then stir to combine. Cover with a lid and remove from heat.
Set aside until the water has absorbed, 5 minutes.

• Cut cucumber into bite-sized chunks. Pick mint leaves and roughly slice.
• In a small bowl, combine cucumber, mint and yoghurt. Season.
• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef strips and Mumbai spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Season.

• Return the frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches until browned and cooked through,
1-2 minutes. Remove from heat, then add mango chutney. Toss to coat.

• Divide carrot couscous between bowls.
• Top with mango-glazed Mumbai beef strips and toasted almonds.
• Serve with cucumber yoghurt.